1
00:01:20,479 --> 00:01:22,037
Is this the last one?

2
00:01:22,279 --> 00:01:24,873
I don't know.
There's no ether, either.

3
00:01:25,439 --> 00:01:27,077
Jesus Christ.

4
00:01:27,639 --> 00:01:30,199
You there!
Is this the last one?

5
00:01:37,039 --> 00:01:38,757
God, what a mess.

6
00:01:39,639 --> 00:01:41,595
At least there's no gangrene.

7
00:01:41,799 --> 00:01:44,154
There will be
if it doesn't come off.

8
00:01:44,319 --> 00:01:46,787
I can't saw if
I can't keep my eyes open.

9
00:01:48,759 --> 00:01:50,158
I'm sorry.

10
00:01:51,479 --> 00:01:53,947
Let's coffee up.
He can wait a few minutes.

11
00:04:32,959 --> 00:04:35,393
- Is that Tucker's men?
- Yes, sir, I think it is.

12
00:04:36,279 --> 00:04:37,837
How long has it been like this?

13
00:04:37,999 --> 00:04:41,150
We just found them this morning.
They been here for 2 days.

14
00:04:51,679 --> 00:04:52,998
Is that you, Lieutenant?

15
00:05:02,479 --> 00:05:04,276
Hey, come on,
you better take cover.

16
00:05:05,359 --> 00:05:06,838
These boys are shooters.

17
00:05:07,399 --> 00:05:08,832
Go under cover.

18
00:05:17,319 --> 00:05:18,877
You went to hospital?

19
00:05:20,759 --> 00:05:22,317
It was no good.

20
00:05:25,639 --> 00:05:27,357
What's going on here?

21
00:05:27,919 --> 00:05:29,477
What's going on here...

22
00:05:29,799 --> 00:05:31,790
is the question all right.

23
00:05:32,959 --> 00:05:35,427
See, you could ask the major.

24
00:05:35,919 --> 00:05:38,194
But he don't know, he's busy.

25
00:05:39,079 --> 00:05:40,910
He's figuring out why

26
00:05:41,079 --> 00:05:43,513
the officer's mess ran out
of ice cream.

27
00:05:44,519 --> 00:05:46,191
And of course you got the general.

28
00:05:46,679 --> 00:05:50,433
He came to see the show.
All he knows is there ain't no show.

29
00:05:52,399 --> 00:05:54,390
The major is looking at
the general,

30
00:05:56,239 --> 00:05:58,275
thinking: "I better do something".

31
00:05:59,479 --> 00:06:01,117
You know what that means.

32
00:06:01,279 --> 00:06:04,032
I don't want to be
the first across this field.

33
00:06:04,279 --> 00:06:06,713
They're supposed to be
beat up like us.

34
00:06:07,879 --> 00:06:09,915
Tucker's men are as tough as cobs.

35
00:06:11,399 --> 00:06:12,878
Only thing killed so far

36
00:06:13,039 --> 00:06:14,950
is three milking cows.

37
00:06:16,239 --> 00:06:17,991
But that's about to change.

38
00:06:22,959 --> 00:06:24,551
You son of a bitch.

39
00:06:25,959 --> 00:06:29,156
Some of the boys are saying,
if we ain't gonna fight,

40
00:06:31,079 --> 00:06:35,231
we could settle all this
with a little high-stakes poker.

41
00:06:35,479 --> 00:06:39,438
Wouldn't that be a sight? A bunch
of fellows sitting in this field,

42
00:06:40,799 --> 00:06:42,232
drawing cards.

43
00:06:50,839 --> 00:06:51,954
What is it?

44
00:06:52,559 --> 00:06:54,231
Looks like a suicide.

45
00:06:54,599 --> 00:06:55,714
Tucker!

46
00:07:35,279 --> 00:07:36,837
What'd you say to him?

47
00:07:37,039 --> 00:07:38,552
I didn't say nothing.

48
00:08:01,559 --> 00:08:03,356
Come on back, you son of a bitch!

49
00:08:03,519 --> 00:08:04,747
Come on back!

50
00:08:06,239 --> 00:08:08,799
- You won't make it a second time!
- All right by me.

51
00:08:11,959 --> 00:08:13,233
Forgive me, Father.

52
00:08:53,559 --> 00:08:55,277
- Ray!
- I got him.

53
00:10:19,639 --> 00:10:20,708
No...

54
00:10:21,839 --> 00:10:24,672
Don't take off my foot.

55
00:10:25,119 --> 00:10:27,633
Rest easy. You'll keep your foot.

56
00:10:28,199 --> 00:10:29,837
I swear you'll keep it.

57
00:10:36,319 --> 00:10:37,957
- Bring up my ambulance.
- Sir?

58
00:10:38,119 --> 00:10:41,031
Bring up my ambulance
and my surgeon with it!

59
00:10:42,399 --> 00:10:45,232
We got an officer
who's worth something here.

60
00:11:11,639 --> 00:11:14,312
The strangeness of life
cannot be measured,

61
00:11:14,479 --> 00:11:18,631
In trying to produce my death,
I was elevated to a living hero,

62
00:11:18,839 --> 00:11:23,276
I was awarded Cisco, the mount
I rode across the field that day,

63
00:11:23,439 --> 00:11:25,999
On recovery, I was given transfer

64
00:11:26,159 --> 00:11:27,433
to any station I desired,

65
00:11:27,599 --> 00:11:30,909
The slaughter continues in the east
as I arrive at Fort Hays,

66
00:11:31,079 --> 00:11:35,357
an island of men and material
surrounded by prairie,

67
00:12:46,279 --> 00:12:48,918
Lieutenant John J. Dunbar.

68
00:12:52,999 --> 00:12:54,637
Lieutenant John J. Dunbar?

69
00:12:55,399 --> 00:12:56,434
Yes, sir.

70
00:12:56,639 --> 00:12:57,788
"Yes, sir".

71
00:12:58,759 --> 00:13:00,033
Indian fighter, huh?

72
00:13:01,239 --> 00:13:02,274
Excuse me?

73
00:13:02,919 --> 00:13:06,355
You're posted to the frontier.
Frontier is Indian country.

74
00:13:06,519 --> 00:13:08,794
I deduce you're an Indian fighter.

75
00:13:08,959 --> 00:13:12,031
- I didn't get promoted being stupid.
- No, sir.

76
00:13:12,439 --> 00:13:13,667
"No, sir".

77
00:13:18,119 --> 00:13:19,234
It says here...

78
00:13:20,079 --> 00:13:22,149
- you've been decorated.
- Yes, sir.

79
00:13:25,039 --> 00:13:26,836
And they posted you here?

80
00:13:27,239 --> 00:13:29,309
I'm here at my own request.

81
00:13:30,039 --> 00:13:32,030
Really? Why?

82
00:13:32,639 --> 00:13:34,630
I've wanted to see the frontier.

83
00:13:35,599 --> 00:13:37,476
You want to see the frontier?

84
00:13:38,039 --> 00:13:39,267
Yes, sir.

85
00:13:39,559 --> 00:13:41,038
Before it's gone.

86
00:13:47,319 --> 00:13:49,116
A smart lad coming to me.

87
00:13:56,199 --> 00:13:59,032
Sir Knight,

88
00:14:00,679 --> 00:14:03,193
I am sending you
on a knight's errand.

89
00:14:04,519 --> 00:14:06,635
Report to Captain Cargill

90
00:14:07,039 --> 00:14:09,394
at the furthermost outpost
of the realm.

91
00:14:09,959 --> 00:14:11,233
Fort Sedgewick.

92
00:14:13,599 --> 00:14:15,590
My personal seal will assure

93
00:14:15,759 --> 00:14:19,911
your safety through many miles
of wild and hostile country.

94
00:14:29,559 --> 00:14:31,515
- I was wondering...
- Yes?

95
00:14:32,359 --> 00:14:34,429
How will I be getting there?

96
00:14:36,279 --> 00:14:37,632
You think I don't know?

97
00:14:38,359 --> 00:14:39,917
- No, sir.
- You think I don't know.

98
00:14:40,079 --> 00:14:42,070
- It's just I don't know.
- Hold your tongue.

99
00:14:42,239 --> 00:14:46,027
I'm generous and will grant
your boon. See that peasant?

100
00:14:47,039 --> 00:14:48,677
He calls himself Timmons.

101
00:14:48,959 --> 00:14:52,349
He's going to Fort Sedgewick.
You can ride with him.

102
00:14:52,919 --> 00:14:55,274
He knows the way.
That is all.

103
00:15:08,079 --> 00:15:09,512
Sir Knight.

104
00:15:13,119 --> 00:15:15,235
I just pissed in my pants.

105
00:15:17,199 --> 00:15:19,713
And nobody can do
anything about it.

106
00:15:33,559 --> 00:15:34,912
To your journey!

107
00:15:39,879 --> 00:15:41,631
To my journey!

108
00:16:13,759 --> 00:16:15,636
The king is dead.

109
00:16:20,239 --> 00:16:22,195
Long live the king.

110
00:17:37,159 --> 00:17:38,194
What you got?

111
00:17:49,279 --> 00:17:53,397
Somebody back east is saying,
"Why don't he write?".

112
00:17:55,159 --> 00:17:57,195
Stupid bastard.

113
00:18:27,439 --> 00:18:28,792
What's that?

114
00:18:29,919 --> 00:18:31,238
What is that?

115
00:18:36,679 --> 00:18:38,351
What the hell is that?

116
00:19:03,919 --> 00:19:05,637
Why don't you put that
in your book?

117
00:19:14,279 --> 00:19:16,349
If not for my companion,
I'd be having

118
00:19:16,519 --> 00:19:18,191
the time of my life,

119
00:19:18,479 --> 00:19:20,913
He means well,

120
00:19:21,079 --> 00:19:23,309
but he is possibly the foulest man
I have ever met,

121
00:19:59,359 --> 00:20:00,792
Get up, Timmons.

122
00:20:02,519 --> 00:20:03,554
Timmons.

123
00:20:04,639 --> 00:20:05,754
Get up.

124
00:20:18,679 --> 00:20:19,873
Get up.

125
00:20:20,959 --> 00:20:22,358
Come on, get up.

126
00:20:33,879 --> 00:20:35,915
Did you poke me in my butt?

127
00:20:37,039 --> 00:20:38,518
Goddamn it!

128
00:20:40,479 --> 00:20:42,117
I'm gonna have a welt.

129
00:21:39,959 --> 00:21:42,189
Why haven't we seen any buffalo?

130
00:21:42,399 --> 00:21:45,277
You can't figure
the stinking buffalo.

131
00:21:45,559 --> 00:21:48,312
Sometimes you won't see any
for days.

132
00:21:48,479 --> 00:21:51,869
Other times, they'll be thick
as curls on a whore.

133
00:21:54,679 --> 00:21:55,828
What about Indians?

134
00:21:56,119 --> 00:21:58,633
Indians? Goddamn Indians.

135
00:21:58,799 --> 00:22:01,597
You'd just as soon not see them
unless they're dead.

136
00:22:02,319 --> 00:22:04,514
They're nothing but
thieves and beggars.

137
00:22:35,719 --> 00:22:39,189
Not what you would call much
of a going concern, is it?

138
00:22:43,519 --> 00:22:45,032
Go down there.

139
00:22:45,239 --> 00:22:47,673
- Why? There's nothing down there.
- Because I said.

140
00:22:49,239 --> 00:22:50,513
Go down there.

141
00:22:55,559 --> 00:22:57,072
Son of a bitch!

142
00:23:22,399 --> 00:23:24,515
There ain't nothing here.

143
00:23:44,119 --> 00:23:46,110
There ain't nothing here,
Lieutenant.

144
00:23:51,039 --> 00:23:52,108
Lieutenant!

145
00:23:53,839 --> 00:23:56,069
Everybody's run off or got killed.

146
00:24:13,159 --> 00:24:14,114
All right.

147
00:24:14,599 --> 00:24:16,237
Let's unload the wagon.

148
00:24:17,359 --> 00:24:18,792
And leave it all here?

149
00:24:21,039 --> 00:24:22,108
I'm staying, too.

150
00:24:22,999 --> 00:24:25,069
There ain't nothing here!

151
00:24:25,719 --> 00:24:28,074
No. Not at the moment.

152
00:24:28,479 --> 00:24:29,878
We don't know what happened.

153
00:24:30,439 --> 00:24:34,637
Things being as they are,

154
00:24:35,039 --> 00:24:36,950
we might as well turn around
and head back.

155
00:24:37,959 --> 00:24:39,631
This is my post.

156
00:24:39,799 --> 00:24:42,074
- "This is my post"?
- This is my post.

157
00:24:44,079 --> 00:24:47,116
"This is my post".
Jesus H. Christ.

158
00:24:47,279 --> 00:24:49,918
Are you crazy, boy? Lieutenant?

159
00:24:52,559 --> 00:24:53,878
That son of a bitch.

160
00:24:55,079 --> 00:24:56,797
- Jesus H. Christ!
- This is my post.

161
00:24:56,959 --> 00:24:58,472
Put it down.

162
00:24:58,639 --> 00:25:00,038
These are the post's provisions.

163
00:25:00,199 --> 00:25:03,475
Get off the wagon
and help me unload.

164
00:25:03,879 --> 00:25:05,870
We're just talking. Put it down.

165
00:25:55,759 --> 00:25:57,351
I'll tell them where you are.

166
00:25:58,599 --> 00:25:59,714
Good.

167
00:26:02,239 --> 00:26:03,513
Good luck, Lieutenant.

168
00:26:05,639 --> 00:26:06,674
Thank you.

169
00:27:06,959 --> 00:27:09,348
Have found Fort Sedgewick deserted,

170
00:27:09,759 --> 00:27:13,229
Am waiting for garrison's return
or word from headquarters,

171
00:27:13,399 --> 00:27:15,390
The post is in poor condition,

172
00:27:15,559 --> 00:27:19,108
I have assigned myself clean-up duty
beginning tomorrow,

173
00:27:19,439 --> 00:27:23,637
Supplies are abundant, the country
is all I dreamed it would be,

174
00:27:24,039 --> 00:27:26,633
There can be no place like this
on earth,

175
00:28:23,559 --> 00:28:24,912
Bad horse.

176
00:28:25,439 --> 00:28:26,872
Bad horse.

177
00:30:01,959 --> 00:30:03,790
Come on, Cisco, one more time.

178
00:30:04,079 --> 00:30:05,307
Get up, Cisco.

179
00:30:06,999 --> 00:30:08,034
Get up, Cisco.

180
00:30:14,079 --> 00:30:15,398
Get up. There you go.

181
00:30:52,319 --> 00:30:55,470
Only a white man would make a fire

182
00:30:55,999 --> 00:30:58,718
for everyone to see,

183
00:30:59,359 --> 00:31:01,111
Maybe there's more than one,

184
00:31:01,919 --> 00:31:04,308
There might be three or four,

185
00:31:05,319 --> 00:31:08,277
I know three or four who will not
be making the trip back home,

186
00:31:08,959 --> 00:31:11,917
We have nothing to show for
this trail,

187
00:31:13,279 --> 00:31:16,476
We have no rifles,
White men are sure to have rifles,

188
00:31:18,999 --> 00:31:22,469
It's hard to say how many
might be down there,

189
00:31:28,799 --> 00:31:31,359
We should forget this and go home,

190
00:31:31,999 --> 00:31:33,273
Then go,

191
00:31:34,519 --> 00:31:35,793
I would rather die

192
00:31:36,559 --> 00:31:38,709
than argue about a single line

193
00:31:38,879 --> 00:31:39,948
of smoke

194
00:31:40,599 --> 00:31:41,827
in my country,

195
00:31:50,199 --> 00:31:51,188
He will not quit

196
00:31:51,359 --> 00:31:53,668
until we are all dead,

197
00:33:13,159 --> 00:33:14,831
Oh, look at me.

198
00:33:23,919 --> 00:33:25,352
Don't hurt my mules.

199
00:33:30,679 --> 00:33:33,034
Stop. Stop it.

200
00:33:39,359 --> 00:33:41,668
Please don't hurt my mules.

201
00:34:39,439 --> 00:34:41,999
Men had been living in these caves,
Why?

202
00:34:42,319 --> 00:34:45,038
Were they frightened?
Had there been some revolt?

203
00:34:45,839 --> 00:34:48,069
I can make no sense
of the clues left here,

204
00:34:48,719 --> 00:34:50,789
Perhaps my relief
will provide the answers,

205
00:35:41,839 --> 00:35:43,750
It's been almost 30 days,

206
00:35:43,919 --> 00:35:45,193
Still no sign of Captain

207
00:35:45,679 --> 00:35:46,634
Cargill's command,

208
00:35:47,599 --> 00:35:49,032
Communications can take place

209
00:35:49,519 --> 00:35:52,079
only if I leave, and I don't want
to abandon my post,

210
00:35:53,039 --> 00:35:54,950
I've decided to ration my goods

211
00:35:55,439 --> 00:35:58,636
as if I were part of a post
rather than the whole affair,

212
00:36:00,399 --> 00:36:02,959
There is a wolf who's intent
on the goings on here,

213
00:36:03,599 --> 00:36:05,510
He's not inclined to be a nuisance,

214
00:36:06,159 --> 00:36:09,356
And aside from Cisco,
he's been my only company,

215
00:36:09,679 --> 00:36:11,749
He's come each afternoon
for two days,

216
00:36:13,199 --> 00:36:15,110
He has milky white socks
on both feet,

217
00:36:15,759 --> 00:36:19,115
If he comes calling tomorrow,
I will name him Two Socks,

218
00:38:39,519 --> 00:38:40,508
You there!

219
00:39:26,439 --> 00:39:28,748
Have made first contact
with an Indian,

220
00:39:29,159 --> 00:39:30,990
One came and tried to steal
my horse,

221
00:39:31,919 --> 00:39:34,672
When I appeared, he became
frightened and ran off,

222
00:39:35,439 --> 00:39:37,236
I don't know how many there are,

223
00:39:37,399 --> 00:39:39,959
but where there's one,
there's another,

224
00:39:41,359 --> 00:39:42,235
I have decided

225
00:39:42,399 --> 00:39:45,550
to bury excess ordnance
lest it fall into enemy hands,

226
00:39:46,319 --> 00:39:49,868
My rides have been reduced
to short patrols,

227
00:39:50,199 --> 00:39:51,791
always in sight of the fort,

228
00:39:53,079 --> 00:39:54,353
I am still alone, however,

229
00:39:54,999 --> 00:39:57,229
Unless troops arrives soon,
all may be lost,

230
00:40:05,239 --> 00:40:06,991
It's been two days and nothing,

231
00:40:07,639 --> 00:40:10,028
My presence must have been reported,

232
00:40:10,519 --> 00:40:12,908
I have made all preparations
I can think of,

233
00:40:13,359 --> 00:40:15,156
Cannot mount an adequate defense

234
00:40:15,639 --> 00:40:18,028
but will try to make a big
impression when they come,

235
00:40:18,359 --> 00:40:18,996
Waiting,

236
00:40:20,119 --> 00:40:20,915
Postscript,

237
00:40:21,559 --> 00:40:24,596
The man I encountered was
a magnificent-looking fellow,

238
00:40:29,559 --> 00:40:31,470
I do not care for this talk
about a white man,

239
00:40:32,439 --> 00:40:33,713
Whatever he is,

240
00:40:34,039 --> 00:40:37,270
he is not Sioux,
and that makes him less,

241
00:40:37,639 --> 00:40:39,630
When I hear that more whites
are coming, I want to laugh,

242
00:40:39,799 --> 00:40:43,155
We took a hundred horses
from these people,

243
00:40:43,479 --> 00:40:44,912
There was no honor in it,

244
00:40:45,399 --> 00:40:48,755
They don't ride well, They don't
shoot well, They're dirty,

245
00:40:50,199 --> 00:40:53,714
These soldiers could not even
make it through one winter here,

246
00:40:54,679 --> 00:40:58,638
These people are said to flourish?
I think they will all be dead soon,

247
00:41:01,399 --> 00:41:04,118
I think this fool is probably lost,

248
00:41:09,799 --> 00:41:12,916
Wind In His Hair's words
are strong and I have heard them,

249
00:41:13,559 --> 00:41:16,119
It's true the whites are a poor race
and hard to understand,

250
00:41:17,239 --> 00:41:18,308
But make no mistake,

251
00:41:18,479 --> 00:41:20,117
The whites are coming,

252
00:41:20,279 --> 00:41:21,871
Even our enemies agree on this,

253
00:41:22,199 --> 00:41:25,669
So when I see one man alone
without fear in our country,

254
00:41:25,879 --> 00:41:27,153
I do not think he is lost,

255
00:41:28,119 --> 00:41:29,871
I think he may have medicine,

256
00:41:30,839 --> 00:41:33,399
I see someone who might speak for

257
00:41:33,719 --> 00:41:35,949
all the white people
who are coming,

258
00:41:36,759 --> 00:41:39,956
I think this is a person with
which treaties might be struck,

259
00:41:43,159 --> 00:41:43,796
I have heard,

260
00:41:45,399 --> 00:41:48,277
Kicking Bird is always
looking ahead,

261
00:41:48,439 --> 00:41:49,667
and that is good,

262
00:41:49,879 --> 00:41:53,554
But this man cannot cover
our lodges or feed our children,

263
00:41:54,199 --> 00:41:56,269
He is nothing to us,

264
00:41:57,559 --> 00:41:59,151
I will take some men,

