01:20:56,079 --> 01:20:58,354
with no regard for Sioux rites,

540
01:20:58,759 --> 01:21:01,432
The wagon tracks left little doubt,

541
01:21:01,599 --> 01:21:03,715
My heart sank as I knew

542
01:21:03,879 --> 01:21:05,198
it was white hunters,

543
01:21:05,799 --> 01:21:09,474
Voices that had been joyous
were silent as the dead buffalo

544
01:21:09,639 --> 01:21:11,357
were left to rot,

545
01:21:11,519 --> 01:21:14,670
killed only for their tongues
and the price of their hides,

546
01:21:22,839 --> 01:21:25,672
As they celebrated the coming hunt,

547
01:21:25,959 --> 01:21:27,995
it was hard to know where to be,

548
01:21:28,639 --> 01:21:32,154
I don't know if they understood,
but I couldn't sleep among them,

549
01:21:32,439 --> 01:21:35,511
There had been no looks
and no blame,

550
01:21:35,799 --> 01:21:39,394
Only the confusion of people
not able to predict the future,

551
01:28:57,079 --> 01:28:59,354
Are you all right?

552
01:30:44,279 --> 01:30:45,678
I can't.

553
01:30:46,759 --> 01:30:49,148
No, I'm full.

554
01:30:49,319 --> 01:30:52,516
I'm full. And I can't tell
the story any more.

555
01:31:01,879 --> 01:31:03,392
You want to try it?

556
01:31:04,359 --> 01:31:05,633
You want to try it?

557
01:31:09,519 --> 01:31:10,634
Here.

558
01:31:39,079 --> 01:31:40,194
I can't.

559
01:31:40,359 --> 01:31:41,553
This is too much.

560
01:31:47,679 --> 01:31:48,748
Good trade.

561
01:31:52,119 --> 01:31:54,269
This is a good trade.

562
01:31:59,199 --> 01:32:02,350
No, I can't. I'm full.
I'm tired.

563
01:32:22,519 --> 01:32:23,554
Tatanka,

564
01:32:23,719 --> 01:32:25,994
Big tatanka,

565
01:32:26,199 --> 01:32:27,473
Big tatanka,

566
01:32:54,799 --> 01:32:55,993
That's my hat.

567
01:33:05,959 --> 01:33:07,631
You're wearing my hat.

568
01:33:11,479 --> 01:33:12,628
It's my hat.

569
01:33:13,159 --> 01:33:15,548
I found it on the prairie,
It's mine,

570
01:33:20,679 --> 01:33:21,794
My hat.

571
01:33:40,159 --> 01:33:44,152
That hat belongs to the Lieutenant,

572
01:33:44,319 --> 01:33:46,469
He left it on the prairie,

573
01:33:46,799 --> 01:33:48,152
He didn't want it,

574
01:33:50,199 --> 01:33:52,190
Well, you can see

575
01:33:52,519 --> 01:33:53,474
he wants it now,

576
01:33:54,639 --> 01:33:58,518
We all know that
it's a soldier's hat,

577
01:33:59,879 --> 01:34:00,948
We all know

578
01:34:01,119 --> 01:34:02,677
who wears it,

579
01:34:03,639 --> 01:34:05,834
If you want to keep it,
that's all right,

580
01:34:05,999 --> 01:34:07,273
But give something for it,

581
01:34:41,919 --> 01:34:44,069
Good trade.

582
01:36:49,999 --> 01:36:52,797
It seems every day ends
with a miracle here,

583
01:36:53,319 --> 01:36:56,550
Whatever God may be,
I thank God for this day,

584
01:36:57,079 --> 01:36:59,388
To stay longer
would've been useless,

585
01:36:59,639 --> 01:37:02,107
We had all the meat
we could possibly carry,

586
01:37:02,519 --> 01:37:05,431
We had hunted for 3 days,
losing 6 ponies,

587
01:37:05,599 --> 01:37:07,317
And only 3 men injured,

588
01:37:08,039 --> 01:37:11,668
I'd never known people
so eager to laugh,

589
01:37:11,839 --> 01:37:12,749
so devoted to family,

590
01:37:12,919 --> 01:37:16,753
so dedicated to each other, The word
that came to mind was "harmony",

591
01:37:25,719 --> 01:37:28,870
Many times I've felt lonely,
But until this afternoon,

592
01:37:29,039 --> 01:37:32,349
I'd never felt completely lonely,

593
01:38:42,239 --> 01:38:44,309
Though only 2 days,
it seems like a week,

594
01:38:44,479 --> 01:38:46,788
I am missing the company
of my new friends,

595
01:38:47,319 --> 01:38:50,072
I can see all their faces,
but it is not enough,

596
01:38:50,359 --> 01:38:52,589
Tomorrow I will make a visit,

597
01:38:52,759 --> 01:38:55,068
They are my neighbors,
What can it hurt?

598
01:39:10,799 --> 01:39:12,596
Go home!

599
01:39:17,999 --> 01:39:19,068
Go!

600
01:39:19,279 --> 01:39:20,871
Go home, Two Socks.

601
01:39:22,319 --> 01:39:24,196
Bad wolf. Bad wolf.

602
01:40:01,959 --> 01:40:05,713
It is autumn, and I am spending
more time with my friends,

603
01:40:05,919 --> 01:40:09,150
They have given me my own lodge
and I feel comfortable,

604
01:40:09,479 --> 01:40:10,798
We talk every day,

605
01:40:10,959 --> 01:40:13,314
but Kicking Bird
is frustrated with me,

606
01:40:13,479 --> 01:40:16,915
He wants to know how many more
white people are coming,

607
01:40:17,119 --> 01:40:20,509
I tell him white people
will only pass through

608
01:40:20,719 --> 01:40:23,836
this country,
But I am speaking in half-truths,

609
01:40:23,999 --> 01:40:27,196
One day there will be too many,
But I cannot tell him that,

610
01:40:28,479 --> 01:40:31,710
I am sure Stands with a Fist
knows I am holding back,

611
01:40:32,279 --> 01:40:34,190
But she says nothing,

612
01:41:01,919 --> 01:41:05,707
A war party is going against
the Pawnee, I have asked to go,

613
01:41:05,879 --> 01:41:08,188
I sensed that I made a mistake
in doing so,

614
01:41:08,359 --> 01:41:10,748
But I didn't take it back,

615
01:41:10,999 --> 01:41:15,515
They are my friends, and the Pawnee
have been very hard on them,

616
01:41:15,919 --> 01:41:18,433
I hope I have not overstepped
my bounds,

617
01:41:22,639 --> 01:41:24,277
Come in, please.

618
01:41:26,679 --> 01:41:27,794
Sit down.

619
01:41:31,199 --> 01:41:33,429
Kicking Bird wants to know

620
01:41:33,599 --> 01:41:37,035
why you want to make war
on the Pawnee.

621
01:41:37,359 --> 01:41:39,998
They have done nothing to you.

622
01:41:40,679 --> 01:41:42,112
They are Sioux enemies.

623
01:41:51,399 --> 01:41:53,117
Only Sioux warriors to go.

624
01:41:53,519 --> 01:41:56,238
Tell him I have been a warrior
longer than many

625
01:41:56,399 --> 01:41:59,516
of the young men who will go
on the war party.

626
01:42:14,079 --> 01:42:18,311
He says the Sioux way
of being a warrior

627
01:42:18,479 --> 01:42:21,516
is not the white way.
You are not ready.

628
01:42:21,679 --> 01:42:25,115
I know. But tell him
I cannot learn these ways in camp.

629
01:42:32,999 --> 01:42:35,559
He also asks that you

630
01:42:36,399 --> 01:42:37,957
watch over his family

631
01:42:38,119 --> 01:42:39,711
while he is gone.

632
01:42:41,159 --> 01:42:43,229
This thing he asks is
a great honor

633
01:42:43,399 --> 01:42:44,752
for you.

634
01:42:47,359 --> 01:42:50,590
I would be happy
to watch over his family.

635
01:42:57,319 --> 01:42:59,469
He thanks Dances With Wolves
for coming.

636
01:43:01,439 --> 01:43:03,031
Who is Dances With Wolves?

637
01:43:05,279 --> 01:43:07,793
It is the name which

638
01:43:07,959 --> 01:43:10,109
the people are calling you now.

639
01:43:10,959 --> 01:43:13,427
Dances With Wolves.

640
01:43:13,719 --> 01:43:15,038
That's right.

641
01:43:15,479 --> 01:43:16,673
That day.

642
01:43:17,919 --> 01:43:19,716
Dances With Wolves.

643
01:43:21,039 --> 01:43:22,267
How do you say it?

644
01:43:57,639 --> 01:44:00,631
Keep on with the white man talk,

645
01:44:00,839 --> 01:44:02,750
if it pleases you,

646
01:44:02,919 --> 01:44:05,308
I like to make the talk,

647
01:44:42,799 --> 01:44:46,269
Oh, I cut this off today.
I shaved it off.

648
01:44:46,599 --> 01:44:47,748
Go on.

649
01:44:49,359 --> 01:44:51,190
Grass grows on the prairie.

650
01:44:54,959 --> 01:44:56,312
Wrong.

651
01:44:56,479 --> 01:44:59,039
You said,
"Fire lives on the prairie".

652
01:44:59,199 --> 01:44:59,631
I did?

653
01:45:00,759 --> 01:45:02,909
No laughing now.

654
01:45:14,799 --> 01:45:16,312
How did you get your name?

655
01:45:20,999 --> 01:45:23,797
I was not very old...

656
01:45:24,559 --> 01:45:26,993
when I came to be with our people.

657
01:45:27,839 --> 01:45:29,909
And I was made to work.

658
01:45:30,639 --> 01:45:33,028
I worked every day very hard.

659
01:45:34,639 --> 01:45:37,756
And there was one woman

660
01:45:37,919 --> 01:45:39,989
who didn't like me much.

661
01:45:41,399 --> 01:45:45,187
She used to call me bad names
and sometimes she...

662
01:45:49,519 --> 01:45:50,838
beat me.

663
01:45:54,479 --> 01:45:59,269
One day, she was calling me
these bad names...

664
01:45:59,439 --> 01:46:01,669
with her face in my face.

665
01:46:02,719 --> 01:46:04,072
And I hit her.

666
01:46:05,839 --> 01:46:08,876
I was not very big,
but she fell down.

667
01:46:09,119 --> 01:46:11,587
She fell hard and didn't move.

668
01:46:12,639 --> 01:46:17,030
And I stood over her with my fist
and asked

669
01:46:17,759 --> 01:46:20,227
if there was any other woman

670
01:46:20,559 --> 01:46:23,198
who wanted to call me bad names.

671
01:46:24,519 --> 01:46:27,192
No one bothered me after that day.

672
01:46:29,799 --> 01:46:32,313
No, I wouldn't think so.

673
01:46:37,479 --> 01:46:38,594
Show me.

674
01:46:39,799 --> 01:46:41,790
Show me where you hit her.

675
01:47:09,359 --> 01:47:11,031
Why are you not married?

676
01:47:14,879 --> 01:47:16,870
- I'm sorry.
- I have to go.

677
01:47:18,999 --> 01:47:20,193
I'm sorry.

678
01:47:22,599 --> 01:47:23,998
- Can I help you?
- No.

679
01:47:43,159 --> 01:47:45,229
Some of your words are wrong,

680
01:47:46,039 --> 01:47:49,076
but you are learning fast,

681
01:47:49,879 --> 01:47:50,834
So,,,

682
01:47:51,479 --> 01:47:54,039
what can I tell you today?

683
01:47:55,319 --> 01:47:57,230
I want to know about
Stands With A Fist,

684
01:47:57,399 --> 01:47:59,629
Why is there no man with her?

685
01:48:02,039 --> 01:48:04,599
She is in mourning,

686
01:48:09,399 --> 01:48:12,436
I do not understand "mourning",

687
01:48:14,199 --> 01:48:16,429
She cries for someone,

688
01:48:18,839 --> 01:48:20,591
Cries for who?

689
01:48:24,599 --> 01:48:26,669
It is not polite
to speak of the dead,

690
01:48:27,319 --> 01:48:28,593
But you are new,

691
01:48:29,239 --> 01:48:30,991
so I will tell you,

692
01:48:31,799 --> 01:48:33,710
She cries for her husband,

693
01:48:33,879 --> 01:48:35,312
He was killed not long ago,

694
01:48:35,639 --> 01:48:38,199
That is how you came to find her
on the prairie

695
01:48:38,839 --> 01:48:39,954
crying,

696
01:48:43,319 --> 01:48:46,834
How long will she cry?

697
01:48:49,079 --> 01:48:50,990
It is Kicking Bird's place to say

698
01:48:52,119 --> 01:48:53,393
when she is finished,

699
01:48:53,879 --> 01:48:56,439
He's the one that found her
when she was very little,

700
01:49:14,359 --> 01:49:16,589
People are talking about you,

701
01:49:19,799 --> 01:49:20,754
What are they saying?

702
01:49:21,719 --> 01:49:23,471
They are proud of

703
01:49:24,279 --> 01:49:26,190
the medicine you are making

704
01:49:26,359 --> 01:49:29,078
with Dances With Wolves,

705
01:49:32,439 --> 01:49:34,350
I have hurt him,

706
01:49:34,519 --> 01:49:36,271
and I should go talk to him,

707
01:49:37,719 --> 01:49:39,630
You can't, He is gone,

708
01:49:41,239 --> 01:49:42,831
He left this morning,

709
01:51:52,319 --> 01:51:53,991
I bet you were thinking,

710
01:51:54,279 --> 01:51:55,871
"Now, why don't he write".

711
01:51:57,159 --> 01:51:58,672
Hello, Two Socks.

712
01:52:24,999 --> 01:52:26,193
Come on.

713
01:52:27,519 --> 01:52:28,554
Come on.

714
01:52:30,799 --> 01:52:33,757
Come on, you can do this.

715
01:52:34,239 --> 01:52:35,433
You can do this.

716
01:52:40,199 --> 01:52:41,314
Come on.

717
01:52:52,799 --> 01:52:54,437
It's easy.

718
01:52:54,639 --> 01:52:56,869
This is easy, Two Socks.

719
01:53:52,759 --> 01:53:54,511
I am in mourning.

720
01:54:03,079 --> 01:54:04,910
No one can know.

721
01:54:06,119 --> 01:54:08,189
We must be careful.

722
01:54:09,799 --> 01:54:11,437
We must be careful.

723
01:57:00,799 --> 01:57:01,914
What?

724
01:57:02,799 --> 01:57:04,198
I don't know.

725
01:57:26,759 --> 01:57:28,989
The Pawnee are coming.
40 or 50 men.

726
01:57:29,159 --> 01:57:31,798
Hunters found them to the north.

727
01:57:31,959 --> 01:57:33,995
- They're heading for our camp.
- Stone Calf, wait,

728
01:57:34,159 --> 01:57:36,275
I will follow you,

729
01:57:36,439 --> 01:57:38,999
The Pawnee do not come for horses,
They come for blood,

730
01:57:39,279 --> 01:57:41,509
Get your weapons
and come to my lodge,

731
01:57:41,679 --> 01:57:42,668
I will go.

732
01:57:43,119 --> 01:57:44,347
I will get them,

733
01:57:44,919 --> 01:57:46,068
Stone Calf, wait,

734
01:57:46,559 --> 01:57:48,231
I have guns,

735
01:57:48,399 --> 01:57:49,798
I have many rifles,

736
01:57:52,319 --> 01:57:54,196
- At the fort?
- Yes.

737
01:57:55,319 --> 01:57:57,469
No, The ride is long
and we can spare no men,

738
01:57:57,799 --> 01:58:00,029
Guns would make one warrior

739
01:58:00,279 --> 01:58:01,473
like two,

740
01:58:06,119 --> 01:58:08,030
Take one man and go quickly,

741
01:58:10,279 --> 01:58:11,553
I will take Smiles A Lot,

742
01:58:12,999 --> 01:58:13,636
Very well,

743
02:01:29,799 --> 02:01:30,595
Shoot the gun!

744
02:05:19,279 --> 02:05:21,474
It was hard to know how to feel,

745
02:05:21,799 --> 02:05:23,710
I had never been
in a battle like this,

746
02:05:24,359 --> 02:05:26,429
There was no
dark political objective,

747
02:05:26,919 --> 02:05:30,594
It was not a fight for territory
or riches or to make men free,

748
02:05:31,079 --> 02:05:34,116
It was fought to preserve
our winter food stores,

749
02:05:34,439 --> 02:05:37,954
to protect the lives
of women and children right here,

750
02:05:39,079 --> 02:05:40,990
Stone Calf was a great loss,

751
02:05:41,639 --> 02:05:43,869
But no one could remember
such a great victory,

752
02:05:44,839 --> 02:05:46,750
I began to look at it
in a new way,

753
02:05:47,879 --> 02:05:49,790
I felt a pride
I had never felt before,

754
02:05:50,919 --> 02:05:53,308
I'd never really known
who John Dunbar was,

755
02:05:54,119 --> 02:05:56,189
Perhaps the name had no meaning,

756
02:05:56,679 --> 02:05:59,239
But as I heard my Sioux name
being called

757
02:05:59,399 --> 02:06:01,788
I knew for the first time
who I really was,

758
02:07:34,239 --> 02:07:37,470
Where are you going?
There is gambling tonight,

759
02:07:37,639 --> 02:07:39,869
Horseback's games are always good,

760
02:07:40,039 --> 02:07:41,313
I'm tired,

761
02:07:41,959 --> 02:07:43,870
Horseback already has

762
02:07:44,039 --> 02:07:46,428
a good rifle of mine,

763
02:07:49,639 --> 02:07:51,709
Good night,

764
02:08:32,759 --> 02:08:35,319
How long will
Stands With A Fist mourn?

765
02:08:36,599 --> 02:08:38,510
I don't know,

766
02:08:42,199 --> 02:08:44,429
I hope it will not be long,

767
02:08:47,159 --> 02:08:49,070
Has something happened?

768
02:08:50,199 --> 02:08:50,995
What?

769
02:08:52,439 --> 02:08:54,350
She has found love again,

770
02:08:56,119 --> 02:08:56,756
With who?

771
02:08:58,039 --> 02:08:59,154
Who do you think?

772
02:08:59,639 --> 02:09:00,435
Tell me,

773
02:09:01,079 --> 02:09:02,671
Dances With Wolves,

774
02:09:06,039 --> 02:09:07,313
Are you certain of this?

775
02:09:08,759 --> 02:09:11,796
When you see them together,
you will know,

776
02:09:14,039 --> 02:09:15,313
What are people saying?

777
02:09:16,439 --> 02:09:18,031
They like the match,

778
02:09:23,479 --> 02:09:24,753
No one is angry?

779
02:09:25,559 --> 02:09:28,596
It makes sense,
They are both white,

780
02:09:31,319 --> 02:09:34,675
I suppose I will be the one
to say something,

781
02:09:36,439 --> 02:09:38,191
She's your daughter now,

782
02:09:39,319 --> 02:09:40,434
I know,

783
02:09:46,519 --> 02:09:49,716
Relax, you can't see
everything coming,

784
02:09:50,999 --> 02:09:51,636
Stop it,

785
02:09:52,279 --> 02:09:53,394
Quit your playing,

786
02:10:07,159 --> 02:10:08,433
Stands With A Fist,

787
02:10:10,039 --> 02:10:11,313
You will mourn no more,

788
02:10:27,319 --> 02:10:28,434
You look good,

789
02:10:29,559 --> 02:10:31,948
You know, the man she mourned for,,,

790
02:10:32,599 --> 02:10:34,510
He was my best friend,

791
02:10:37,079 --> 02:10:38,353
I didn't know that,

792
02:10:41,239 --> 02:10:42,831
He was a good man,

793
02:10:44,119 --> 02:10:46,349
It has been hard for me
to like you,

794
02:10:48,439 --> 02:10:50,669
I am not the thinker
Kicking Bird is,

795
02:10:51,799 --> 02:10:53,710
I always feel anger first,

796
02:10:54,359 --> 02:10:56,270
There were no answers
to my questions,

797
02:10:56,759 --> 02:10:57,874
But now I think

798
02:10:58,359 --> 02:10:59,951
he went away because

799
02:11:00,439 --> 02:11:01,394
you were coming,

800
02:11:01,719 --> 02:11:02,993
That is how I see it,

801
02:11:27,239 --> 02:11:29,389
This is a good day for me,

802
02:11:31,159 --> 02:11:32,114
And for me.

803
02:11:34,759 --> 02:11:38,195
Stands With A Fist,
if you want this man,

804
02:11:38,679 --> 02:11:40,271
take his hand in yours,

805
02:11:53,399 --> 02:11:55,469
I'd never been married,

806
02:11:55,799 --> 02:11:57,391
I don't know if all grooms

807
02:11:57,879 --> 02:11:59,153
feel the same,

808
02:11:59,479 --> 02:12:02,516
but as Kicking Bird described
what was expected

809
02:12:02,999 --> 02:12:06,036
of a Sioux husband, my mind shut out
everything but her,

810
02:12:06,519 --> 02:12:08,271
The tiny details of her costume,

811
02:12:08,919 --> 02:12:10,193
The contours of her shape,

812
02:12:11,159 --> 02:12:12,433
The light in her eyes,

813
02:12:13,079 --> 02:12:14,512
The smallness of her feet,

814
02:12:15,799 --> 02:12:18,029
I knew the love between us
would be served,

815
02:12:19,799 --> 02:12:22,029
Have you heard what I have said?

816
02:12:24,279 --> 02:12:26,998
Have you heard what I have said?

817
02:12:31,319 --> 02:12:32,911
Good, then

818
02:12:33,879 --> 02:12:35,153
take her inside,

819
02:12:36,119 --> 02:12:37,234
She is your wife,

820
02:12:39,959 --> 02:12:40,755
Oh, good.

821
02:12:42,999 --> 02:12:44,591
Thank you,

822
02:13:32,759 --> 02:13:34,989
It's good to be out,

823
02:13:36,279 --> 02:13:37,871
Yes, it must be,

824
02:13:39,479 --> 02:13:41,549
We are trying for a baby,

825
02:13:43,319 --> 02:13:44,274
No waiting?

826
02:13:45,239 --> 02:13:46,513
No waiting,

827
02:13:50,839 --> 02:13:53,228
I was just thinking that
of all the trails

828
02:13:53,719 --> 02:13:55,471
in this life,

829
02:13:56,119 --> 02:13:58,030
there is one that matters most,

830
02:13:59,319 --> 02:14:02,197
It is the trail of a true
human being,

831
02:14:03,639 --> 02:14:04,913
I think you are on this trail,

832
02:14:06,999 --> 02:14:08,273
and it is good to see,

833
02:14:26,999 --> 02:14:28,432
You ride your horse often,

834
02:14:33,239 --> 02:14:33,876
I like that,

835
02:14:48,119 --> 02:14:50,189
You always ask about
the white people,

836
02:14:53,399 --> 02:14:55,310
You always want to know
how many more are coming,

837
02:14:57,719 --> 02:14:59,152
There will be a lot, my friend,

838
02:15:00,279 --> 02:15:01,871
More than can be counted,

839
02:15:04,599 --> 02:15:05,395
How many?

840
02:15:08,439 --> 02:15:09,872
Like the stars.

841
02:15:15,479 --> 02:15:16,753
Like the stars,

842
02:15:23,319 --> 02:15:25,549
It makes me afraid

843
02:15:26,039 --> 02:15:27,313
for all the Sioux,

844
02:15:34,519 --> 02:15:36,908
We should tell this to Ten Bears,

845
02:16:02,359 --> 02:16:04,748
The men who wore this came
in the time of

846
02:16:05,239 --> 02:16:07,150
my Grandfather's Grandfather,

847
02:16:07,799 --> 02:16:08,754
Eventually,

848
02:16:09,239 --> 02:16:10,194
we drove them out,

849
02:16:11,159 --> 02:16:13,719
Then the Mexicans came,
They do not come here any more,

850
02:16:15,319 --> 02:16:16,911
In my own time, the Texans,

851
02:16:18,199 --> 02:16:20,269
They have been like all the others,

852
02:16:23,479 --> 02:16:25,868
They take

853
02:16:26,039 --> 02:16:27,791
without asking,

854
02:16:28,919 --> 02:16:32,434
I don't know if we are ready
for these people,

855
02:16:33,879 --> 02:16:35,153
But I think you are right,

856
02:16:36,119 --> 02:16:38,030
I think they will keep coming,

857
02:16:39,319 --> 02:16:41,230
When I think of that,
I look at this helmet,

858
02:16:44,119 --> 02:16:45,393
Our country is all that we have,

859
02:16:46,039 --> 02:16:47,950
and we will fight to keep it,

860
02:16:49,399 --> 02:16:52,277
Tomorrow we will strike the village
and go to the winter camp,

861
02:17:08,439 --> 02:17:10,999
You have everything
from the soldier fort?

862
02:17:12,599 --> 02:17:14,032
Yes. There's nothing for me there.

863
02:17:15,799 --> 02:17:16,754
That's good.

864
02:17:30,199 --> 02:17:30,995
The journal.

865
02:17:33,559 --> 02:17:34,833
Wait.

866
02:17:35,959 --> 02:17:39,156
The book is like a trail
for people to follow.

867
02:17:39,639 --> 02:17:42,995
It tells everything about
my life here. I must get it.

868
02:17:43,159 --> 02:17:43,796
Enough.

869
02:17:44,119 --> 02:17:46,030
We cannot wait for you.

870
02:17:57,839 --> 02:17:58,988
I'll catch up.

871
02:17:59,279 --> 02:18:00,632
I'll catch up.

872
02:18:38,759 --> 02:18:39,748
Injuns!

873
02:19:10,319 --> 02:19:12,389
Stay down. Stay.

874
02:19:15,039 --> 02:19:16,028
Oh, God.

875
02:19:21,559 --> 02:19:22,628
It's okay.

876
02:20:02,799 --> 02:20:06,314
Something must have happened,
Dances With Wolves is not coming,

877
02:20:07,439 --> 02:20:08,633
He must have trouble,

878
02:20:10,799 --> 02:20:13,188
Algo ha pasado,
no es normal,

879
02:20:13,679 --> 02:20:16,398
Pick two good men and send them
back to the soldier fort,

880
02:20:27,279 --> 02:20:28,075
Spivey.

881
02:20:29,679 --> 02:20:31,590
- Spivey.
- Yeah, Sergeant?

882
02:20:32,719 --> 02:20:34,630
Tell the major he's waking up.

883
02:20:36,719 --> 02:20:37,834
Move your worthless ass.

884
02:20:49,519 --> 02:20:51,430
You got yourself
a hell of a shiner,

885
02:20:51,919 --> 02:20:52,715
didn't you?

886
02:21:05,199 --> 02:21:06,314
Does he speak English?

887
02:21:07,119 --> 02:21:08,074
I don't know, sir.

888
02:21:10,319 --> 02:21:11,274
You speak English?

889
02:21:13,839 --> 02:21:14,794
You talk English?

890
02:21:15,599 --> 02:21:16,395
Talk!

891
02:21:17,999 --> 02:21:19,273
I speak English.

892
02:21:23,919 --> 02:21:24,874
Who are you?

893
02:21:27,279 --> 02:21:30,510
Lieutenant John J. Dunbar.
This is my post.

894
02:21:32,079 --> 02:21:33,353
Why are you dressed like that?

895
02:21:35,759 --> 02:21:38,478
I came out from Fort Hays
last April, but nobody was here.

896
02:21:40,079 --> 02:21:41,034
You have proof of that?

897
02:21:44,399 --> 02:21:46,310
My journal's in my quarters.

898
02:21:46,719 --> 02:21:49,916
My orders are in the journal.
It'll tell you everything.

899
02:21:50,879 --> 02:21:53,268
Spivey, you and Edwards
were the first here.

900
02:21:53,759 --> 02:21:55,829
Did you find a journal?

901
02:21:56,799 --> 02:21:57,914
We didn't find nothing, sir.

902
02:21:58,879 --> 02:21:59,994
Where's Edwards?

903
02:22:01,119 --> 02:22:01,915
He's outside.

904
02:22:06,719 --> 02:22:08,152
He didn't find nothing either.

905
02:22:23,879 --> 02:22:25,437
You turned Injun, didn't you?

906
02:22:26,879 --> 02:22:27,516
Didn't you?

907
02:22:31,519 --> 02:22:34,079
- He's a soldier.
- He's an officer.

908
02:22:34,399 --> 02:22:36,310
Officer? Do you salute him
or shoot him?

909
02:22:45,439 --> 02:22:47,031
Here, you, eyes front.

910
02:22:52,639 --> 02:22:53,913
Eyes front!

911
02:23:48,479 --> 02:23:49,753
Why are you out of uniform?

912
02:23:54,239 --> 02:23:55,831
Why's the army out here?

913
02:23:56,639 --> 02:23:57,913
The Lieutenant
is asking the questions.

914
02:24:05,119 --> 02:24:06,711
We're charged with

915
02:24:10,239 --> 02:24:12,958
apprehending the hostiles,
recovering stolen property,

916
02:24:13,439 --> 02:24:15,509
retrieving white captives
taken in raids.

917
02:24:16,479 --> 02:24:17,594
There are no hostiles.

918
02:24:17,919 --> 02:24:19,511
We'll be the judge of that.

919
02:24:20,159 --> 02:24:21,751
If you guide us to these camps,

920
02:24:22,399 --> 02:24:24,959
your conduct will be reevaluated.

921
02:24:26,079 --> 02:24:27,034
What conduct?

922
02:24:27,679 --> 02:24:28,953
Your status as

923
02:24:29,279 --> 02:24:31,509
a traitor might improve
if you cooperate

924
02:24:31,999 --> 02:24:33,114
with the U.S. Army.

925
02:24:35,679 --> 02:24:37,431
There's nothing for you
to do out here.

926
02:24:41,439 --> 02:24:42,713
Are you willing to cooperate?

927
02:24:46,399 --> 02:24:47,036
Speak up!

928
02:24:50,879 --> 02:24:53,439
I am Dances With Wolves,

929
02:24:56,799 --> 02:24:57,436
What's that?

930
02:24:57,919 --> 02:25:00,149
I am Dances With Wolves!

931
02:25:00,639 --> 02:25:02,709
I have nothing to say to you,

932
02:25:03,039 --> 02:25:05,917
You are not worth talking to,

933
02:25:15,679 --> 02:25:17,909
Form a detail and take this man
to the river.

934
02:25:20,159 --> 02:25:21,274
Let him clean up his face.

935
02:25:24,639 --> 02:25:25,594
Not you, Spivey.

936
02:26:01,599 --> 02:26:02,554
Hey, Spivey.

937
02:26:08,479 --> 02:26:09,434
You got paper?

938
02:26:09,919 --> 02:26:12,308
- What's it to you?
- Well, give me some.

939
02:26:13,439 --> 02:26:14,235
Can you read?

940
02:26:14,719 --> 02:26:17,438
No, I can't read.
You can't read either.

941
02:26:17,919 --> 02:26:19,034
Just give me some.

942
02:26:20,159 --> 02:26:21,751
Give me some!

943
02:26:21,919 --> 02:26:23,671
All right! Hold your horses.

944
02:27:56,639 --> 02:27:57,913
Lap it up, Injun. Lap it up.

945
02:28:02,239 --> 02:28:03,513
Son of a bitch. I'll kill you.

946
02:28:06,559 --> 02:28:07,355
It's all right.

947
02:28:08,639 --> 02:28:09,435
It's all right.

948
02:28:10,559 --> 02:28:11,992
You're just gonna get hungrier.

949
02:28:12,839 --> 02:28:14,397
But maybe that don't matter.

950
02:28:15,359 --> 02:28:17,111
They're gonna ship you
back to Hays.

951
02:28:18,079 --> 02:28:19,353
And once you get there,

952
02:28:19,999 --> 02:28:21,273
they gonna hang you.

953
02:28:24,799 --> 02:28:26,710
Forget about him. Get out of here.

954
02:29:07,999 --> 02:29:09,591
Spivey, what is that?

955
02:29:10,079 --> 02:29:11,831
Looks like he's following us.

956
02:29:12,479 --> 02:29:13,753
Hell, I'm gonna shoot him.

957
02:29:15,839 --> 02:29:16,954
You missed him.

958
02:29:17,279 --> 02:29:18,234
Don't shoot.

959
02:29:18,879 --> 02:29:20,790
- It's my shot.
- Wait, I saw him first.

960
02:29:21,119 --> 02:29:22,711
That stupid bastard
ain't even moving.

961
02:29:24,639 --> 02:29:26,391
Wait a minute, that's my shot.

962
02:29:28,479 --> 02:29:30,390
Get him. He's standing there.

963
02:29:30,719 --> 02:29:32,949
- He ain't hurt, is he?
- Shoot him!

964
02:29:50,479 --> 02:29:51,753
He might've killed you.

965
02:30:20,399 --> 02:30:21,354
I got him!

966
02:30:21,879 --> 02:30:23,551
I got him!

967
02:30:26,159 --> 02:30:27,114
Dead shot, boys. Come on.

968
02:30:28,719 --> 02:30:31,108
Son of a bitch. Get up!

969
02:30:33,519 --> 02:30:34,315
Get up!

970
02:30:35,279 --> 02:30:36,553
I'll kill you.

971
02:30:41,519 --> 02:30:44,238
Stop bashing him or
I'll put shackles on you.

972
02:30:45,039 --> 02:30:45,835
You men get back here!

973
02:30:51,119 --> 02:30:52,234
God damnit.

974
02:31:44,719 --> 02:31:45,834
Let's go.

975
02:32:09,199 --> 02:32:10,154
I don't see nobody.

976
02:38:10,159 --> 02:38:12,229
Dances With Wolves

977
02:38:12,719 --> 02:38:14,789
is quiet these days,

978
02:38:16,399 --> 02:38:17,832
Is his heart bad?

979
02:38:27,439 --> 02:38:30,317
Killing the soldiers at the river

980
02:38:32,879 --> 02:38:34,631
was a good thing,

981
02:38:36,079 --> 02:38:37,990
I did not mind killing those men,
I was glad to do it,

982
02:38:42,479 --> 02:38:44,390
But the soldiers

983
02:38:45,039 --> 02:38:48,076
hate me now,
like they hate no other,

984
02:38:49,359 --> 02:38:51,429
They think I am a traitor,

985
02:38:56,719 --> 02:38:59,108
And they will hunt for me,

986
02:39:00,079 --> 02:39:03,116
And they find me,
they find you,

987
02:39:05,359 --> 02:39:06,474
I think it would be wise

988
02:39:07,119 --> 02:39:08,393
to move the village now,

989
02:39:09,039 --> 02:39:11,109
As soon as possible,

990
02:39:17,839 --> 02:39:18,954
I will be leaving,

991
02:39:22,159 --> 02:39:24,070
I must go and talk with those
who would listen,

992
02:39:31,479 --> 02:39:33,788
Quiet,
You are hurting my ears,

993
02:40:06,639 --> 02:40:08,869
You are the only white man

994
02:40:09,359 --> 02:40:10,314
I have ever known,

995
02:40:10,639 --> 02:40:13,995
I have thought about you a lot,
More than you know,

996
02:40:14,639 --> 02:40:17,517
But I think you are wrong,

997
02:40:18,799 --> 02:40:21,359
The man the soldiers are looking for
no longer exists,

998
02:40:22,319 --> 02:40:23,434
Now there is only

999
02:40:23,919 --> 02:40:26,149
a Sioux named

1000
02:40:26,479 --> 02:40:27,912
Dances With Wolves,

1001
02:40:31,919 --> 02:40:33,352
Let's smoke awhile,

1002
02:40:39,759 --> 02:40:41,829
With Ten Bears,
it was always more than a while,

1003
02:40:42,159 --> 02:40:43,433
Everything he did had a purpose,

1004
02:40:43,759 --> 02:40:45,351
He wanted me to stay,

1005
02:40:45,839 --> 02:40:48,876
But I would be an excuse,
all the army needed

1006
02:40:49,199 --> 02:40:51,429
to find this place,

1007
02:40:51,599 --> 02:40:54,159
I pushed him to move the camp,

1008
02:40:54,479 --> 02:40:57,357
But in the end, he only smiled
and talked of simple pleasures,

1009
02:40:57,679 --> 02:41:01,354
He reminded me that at his age,
a good fire is better than anything,

1010
02:41:02,159 --> 02:41:04,229
Ten Bears was an extraordinary man,

1011
02:41:44,239 --> 02:41:45,513
You have nothing to say?

1012
02:41:48,239 --> 02:41:49,513
What can I tell you?

1013
02:41:51,439 --> 02:41:52,713
Whatever's on your mind.

1014
02:41:59,759 --> 02:42:01,351
You've made the decision.

1015
02:42:05,999 --> 02:42:07,591
My place is with you.

1016
02:42:08,719 --> 02:42:10,152
I go where you go.

1017
02:42:13,679 --> 02:42:14,794
You're not afraid?

1018
02:42:20,399 --> 02:42:22,788
I told Ten Bears we'd leave
when the snow breaks.

1019
02:42:30,479 --> 02:42:31,753
Did you tell everyone?

1020
02:42:36,079 --> 02:42:37,353
Not everyone.

1021
02:43:12,559 --> 02:43:13,833
It's all right,

1022
02:43:46,319 --> 02:43:46,956
You...

1023
02:43:48,399 --> 02:43:49,991
finish your pipe?

1024
02:44:02,799 --> 02:44:03,595
The pipe...

1025
02:44:05,359 --> 02:44:05,996
How...

1026
02:44:07,439 --> 02:44:08,394
does it smoke?

1027
02:44:11,599 --> 02:44:12,873
I've never smoked it.

1028
02:44:24,239 --> 02:44:25,513
We come far,

1029
02:44:25,999 --> 02:44:26,954
you and me.

1030
02:44:29,719 --> 02:44:31,118
I will not forget you.

1031
02:46:15,919 --> 02:46:17,352
Dances With Wolves!

1032
02:46:19,599 --> 02:46:21,510
I am Wind In His Hair,

1033
02:46:22,639 --> 02:46:25,028
Do you see that I am your friend?

1034
02:46:25,679 --> 02:46:27,590
I am your friend!

1035
02:46:29,359 --> 02:46:32,078
Can you see that you will
always be my friend?

